Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 1",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Double-slit experiments with single electrons. ",
 StyleBox["(a)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " The number density of electrons accumulated on the screen exhibits a clear \
interference pattern. ",
 StyleBox["(b)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " A particle detector (gray disk) is located at the upper slit. In this \
case, no interference pattern is observed."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->558165168,ExpressionUUID->"bf5f1d55-1ca8-4e08-b8ff-c7bc7b95e9ee"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Mach-Zehnder Interference", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->584647518,ExpressionUUID->"672851ae-8fa1-4a9a-bf5b-17c9ab1564d7"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"Let", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Qubit", ",", "S"}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[157]:=",
 CellID->950974545,ExpressionUUID->"30a44663-e34a-4dd3-a454-ee6fcb371d6a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To make the point clearer, it is convenient to consider a slightly \
different version with the Mach-Zehnder interferometer in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1995122200"],
 ". In ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1995122200"],
 " (left), a photon is incident on the horizontal optical mode (the lower \
blue arm of the interferometer) and encounters a beam splitter. It can either \
go through the beam splitter to the other side of the horizontal mode or \
reflected into the vertical mode (the upper red arm). The photon after the \
beam splitter is thus in the state of superposition ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "+", 
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"]}], ")"}], "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "325e86cd-b31b-440c-890b-d7138f0a1c36"],
 ", where |0\:27e9 and |1\:27e9 describe the photon in the blue and red arms, \
respectively. In the blue arm, the photon passes through an optical medium \
that causes an additional phase shift of \[Phi]. The state of the photon in \
this stage is given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "+", 
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{"1"},
        "Ket"], 
       SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
        RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], ")"}], "/", 
    SqrtBox["2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "31fd5c96-aee0-4e82-a4a7-8d34a488da3f"],
 ". The two arms are recombined at the second beam splitter, where the photon \
is either transmitted or reflected. The photon is then described by the \
state"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->859394869,ExpressionUUID->"bb04d489-2c8a-4588-9310-20b8c5fef4b0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], "(", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"1", "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
        RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}], "2"], ")"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"], "(", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"1", "-", 
       SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
        RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}], "2"], ")"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"c7f1c9be-1625-4df6-87db-b1f5a2fe2c17"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->461605193,ExpressionUUID->"f9de8f74-1e9b-450c-885d-dd43446435c7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where the additional phase factor of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Minus]", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dfa8f778-3c74-45ce-aa70-2446ce596281"],
 " (phase shift by \[Pi]) for a photon reflected from the red to blue arm is \
responsible for the reflection from an optically hard medium. The photon is \
finally detected by either detectors at the ends of the optical modes. The \
probability to detect the photon in the blue arm is given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->519896637,ExpressionUUID->"5066111a-3d22-4d12-8f49-35b77c34a07c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "0"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
       FractionBox[
        RowBox[{"1", "+", 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}], "2"], 
       "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "2"], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["cos", "2"], "(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"690acf3d-7f1a-4f08-a222-5c487f18a6f2"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1516938670,ExpressionUUID->"214c900b-48ad-44a8-8f1a-e486521b9463"],

Cell["\<\
Similarly, the probability to find the photon in the red arm is given by\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->485742755,ExpressionUUID->"f9a1b173-8051-4b7a-a3b6-88e73713d9e3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "1"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["sin", "2"], "(", 
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8c84241d-470f-4fca-8cc7-cbb4a4668503"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->682230864,ExpressionUUID->"eec4f6de-d230-4d31-88d1-d05ab07c0ee0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Clearly, the photon detection probability in each output port manifests \
interference as the relative phase shift \[Phi] varies. As the analyses of \
the photon states in respective stages suggest, the Mach-Zehnder \
interferometer in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1995122200"],
 " (left) for a photon is an equivalent of the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 3",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1247206449"],
 " (left) for a qubit."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1090493222,ExpressionUUID->"8498845e-c7bd-42e5-8555-91aa805335ef"],

