Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Complete Decoherence", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->1763954588,ExpressionUUID->"303a211c-4d2f-4d1f-85a3-f47b26fbe6ee"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us now consider a variant in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1995122200"],
 " (right). In this experiment, there is a two-level system coupled to the \
upper optical mode. In other words, if the photon is in the red arm, then it \
interacts with a two-level system. As a result of the interaction, the \
two-level system, which is initially prepared in its ground state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cd680acf-54e0-43d7-9527-093067eb7a3d"],
 ", makes a transition to the excited state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eee5f704-8a34-46d4-8224-33718dd16fb4"],
 ". The two-level system is the counterpart of the particle detector behind \
the upper slit in the double-slit experiment in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 1",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#558165168"],
 " (b). Here we will regard it as an environment. The crucial point is that \
unlike the particle detector, one cannot assess the two-level system in this \
experiment. Nevertheless, through the interaction with the photon traveling \
in the upper arm, the two-level system destroys the interference."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->348201381,ExpressionUUID->"689d86e8-4fcc-4a42-9f4f-364d955561da"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tTo see this, let us take a closer look at what happens in the experiment. \
The initial state of the total system consisting of the incident photon and \
the two-level system is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "59560357-aa38-4f16-bd68-f04d162fff39"],
 ". After the beam splitter and the phase-shifter medium, it becomes"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->205961587,ExpressionUUID->"f024abb1-16d0-4743-98c3-c55462b63a14"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{"0"},
         "Ket"], "+", 
        RowBox[{
         TemplateBox[{"1"},
          "Ket"], 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], 
       SqrtBox["2"]], ")"}], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
      "Ket"]}], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{"0"},
        "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
        "Ket"]}], "+", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{"1"},
         "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
         "Ket"]}], 
       SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
        RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], 
     SqrtBox["2"]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "30222c9b-9fa8-48e9-98b7-a89ed2957092"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->835538077,ExpressionUUID->"8ee6ae67-f0e9-4949-a1b4-b7ba15f78d52"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The interaction between the photon and the two-level system causes the \
transition from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4f645098-a616-422a-ad27-16f40ca3cea3"],
 " to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4effe3ea-9d91-482c-a0bf-1060a83abab5"],
 " on the condition that the photon is in the upper arm. It leads to"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1199746251,ExpressionUUID->"84b66d8b-84fd-413b-8d4b-c173718fd143"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
       "Ket"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{"1"},
        "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
        "Ket"]}], 
      SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
       RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f6bacb04-75ed-49e6-973a-8f580ba7bb6a"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->659592202,ExpressionUUID->"ce55d387-c014-4f46-9a11-2122615522ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "for the state of the total system. The process is analogous to the CNOT \
gate in quantum computation. Indeed, the Mach-Zehnder experiment in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1995122200"],
 " (right) with a two-level system coupled to one of the optical mode is \
equivalent to the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 3",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#1247206449"],
 " (right) for two qubits. After the second beam splitter, the quantum state \
is described by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->764979551,ExpressionUUID->"3e55a11a-1b57-4711-9f7e-f577a62e56e5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"0"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
         "Ket"], "+", 
        RowBox[{
         TemplateBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
          "Ket"], 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], "2"], ")"}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{"1"},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
         "Ket"], "-", 
        RowBox[{
         TemplateBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
          "Ket"], 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], "2"], ")"}]}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"c51d7d69-781a-4cfa-883a-10a3c1a73f74"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->800929055,ExpressionUUID->"3944f6d8-919e-4b37-86d1-380bd3592248"],

Cell["\<\
The probability to detect the photon at the output port of the blue arm is \
thus given by\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1195027976,ExpressionUUID->"5282e062-e748-4c02-bd09-f2ed04d666f2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "0"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", "4"], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
         "Bra"], "+", 
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], " ", "\[Phi]"}]], 
         TemplateBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
          "Bra"]}]}], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "0"]},
         "Ket"], "+", 
        RowBox[{
         TemplateBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "1"]},
          "Ket"], 
         SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
          RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Phi]"}]]}]}], ")"}]}], "=", 
     FractionBox["1", "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "27efbc5e-cccc-4a35-b089-21edca85068f"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->567504081,ExpressionUUID->"55bf7da1-9dc6-4cb5-9169-ee99979f2899"],

Cell["\<\
Likewise, the probability to detect the photon in the other arm is\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1476135031,ExpressionUUID->"0af763a6-ff9b-44c5-88d3-5deb5df32a3b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["P", "1"], "=", 
    FractionBox["1", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "826146e6-fabf-480c-be5c-a1fd3f013806"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->887451220,ExpressionUUID->"21ddf3bc-5e59-46af-8340-4756b98745d9"],

Cell["\<\
Whence the photon detection probabilities show no interference effect.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1281117060,ExpressionUUID->"05bb8c95-8479-4693-a9a4-7decfdb90487"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "It is worth noting that the final quantum state is a maximally entangled \
state between the photon and the two-level system (the maximal entanglement \
is even clearer in the ",
 ButtonBox["quantum state before the second beam splitter",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/HowQuantumDecoherenceOccurs#659592202"],
 "). This means that upon tracing out the two-level system, which we cannot \
assess, the density operator describing the quantum state of the photon \
becomes completely random, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", " ", "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{"I", "/", "2"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c0c45d2b-8c58-4c9e-862f-5371be776d66"],
 ", irrespective of the relative phase shift \[Phi]. That is, due to the \
interaction and subsequent entanglement with the two-level system, the photon \
has lost completely the phase coherence in its quantum state."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1544075415,ExpressionUUID->"dc2cddc5-35c5-4ebe-94fb-c8a32e24fb48"],

Cell["\t", "TechNoteText",
 TabFilling->"\[LongDash]\[NegativeThickSpace]",
 TabSpacings->Scaled[1],
 FontColor->GrayLevel[0.85],
 CellID->104268608,ExpressionUUID->"e06e5183-ec17-4e35-947e-0cf0df3e8c3f"],

